        <abstract>
            <p>CD is too ill to write.</p> 
<p>As for natural selection, he is more faithful to PM’s "own original child" than PM is himself. To illustrate, CD relates the metaphor of an architect selecting well-shaped stones and rejecting ill-shaped ones. [See <hi rend="italic">Variation</hi> 2: 431.]</p> 
        </abstract>
